2008 versus 2007consolidated net sales
for 2008 were $30.5billion, up 4percent. this
reflects 10percent sales growth through september30,
partly offset by a 17percent year-over-year sales decline
in the fourth quarter, precipitated by a significant decline in
demand. full year sales reflect a 7percent increase in
local selling prices and 3percent favorable currency
exchange, partly offset by 5percent lower volume and a
1percent reduction from portfolio changes. worldwide sales
volumes reflect a modest increase outside the u.s.driven
by growth in emerging markets, more than offset by significantly
lower volumes in the companys major polymer, chemical,
material, and electronic product lines sold in the u.s.and
western europe.
