the company routinely uses foreign
currency exchange contracts to offset its net exposures, by
currency, related to the foreign currency- denominated monetary
assets and liabilities. the objective of this program is to
maintain an approximately balanced position in foreign
currencies in order to minimize, on an after-tax basis, the
effects of exchange rate changes on net monetary asset
positions. the net pre-tax exchange gains and losses are
partially offset by the associated tax impact.
